The paper deals with the problem of recovering an unknown signal from quadratic measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and scientific computing (cs.SI, cs.NA). The paper also mentions the potential applications of the proposed method in phase-less imaging systems, which further supports the relevance to cs.CV and cs.SI.
